"Huthwelker T., Krieger U.K., Weers U., Peter Th., Lanford W.A.","RBS analysis of trace gas uptake on ice",2002,"Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research, Section B: Beam Interactions with Materials and Atoms","190","1-4",,"47","53",,,10.1016/S0168-583X(01)01265-4,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0036568977&partnerID=40&md5=b25f183ccdc06dbb9c2cb5c3bcc77f4a","Physics Department, University at Albany, State University of New York, 1400 Washington Avenue, Albany, NY 12222, United States; Institute for Atmospheric and Climate Science (IACETH), Hönggerberg HPP, 8093 Zürich, Switzerland","Huthwelker, T., Physics Department, University at Albany, State University of New York, 1400 Washington Avenue, Albany, NY 12222, United States, Institute for Atmospheric and Climate Science (IACETH), Hönggerberg HPP, 8093 Zürich, Switzerland; Krieger, U.K., Institute for Atmospheric and Climate Science (IACETH), Hönggerberg HPP, 8093 Zürich, Switzerland; Weers, U., Institute for Atmospheric and Climate Science (IACETH), Hönggerberg HPP, 8093 Zürich, Switzerland; Peter, Th., Institute for Atmospheric and Climate Science (IACETH), Hönggerberg HPP, 8093 Zürich, Switzerland; Lanford, W.A., Physics Department, University at Albany, State University of New York, 1400 Washington Avenue, Albany, NY 12222, United States","Uptake and reaction of acidic trace gases (HCl, HBr, SO2,...) on atmospheric aerosols is of key interest to environmental problems such as ozone depletion and global warming. While the importance of these reactions is well established, the physical mechanisms involved are subject to current research and scientific controversy. The present paper demonstrates the use of Rutherford backscattering spectroscopy (RBS) to profile elements such as bromine and sulfur on ice surfaces and the application of RBS to study liquid sulfuric acid. The experimental chamber needed for these measurements is described in this paper. © 2002 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved.","Aerosols; Ice; RBS; Sulfuric acid; Surface chemistry","Atmospheric aerosols; Gases; Global warming; Ice; Sulfuric acid; Surface chemistry; Trace analysis; Acidic trace gases; Rutherford backscattering spectroscopy",,,,,,"Charlson, R.J., Schwartz, S.E., Hales, J.M., Cess, R.D., (1992) Science, 255, p. 425; Solomon, S., (1990) Nature, 347, p. 347; Peter, Th., (1997) Ann. Rev. Phys. Chem., 48, p. 785; Legrand, M., Mayewski, P., (1997) Rev. Geophys., 35 (3), p. 219; Wolff, E.W., Bales, R.B., (1996) NATO ASI Series I: Global environmental change, 43. , Springer-Verlag, Berlin; Hanson, D.R., Ravishankara, A.R., (1993) J. Phys. Chem., 255, p. 12309; Abbatt, J.P.D., Beyer, K.D., Fucaloro, A.F., McMahon, J.R., Wooldridge, P.J., Zhang, R., Molina, M.J., (1992) J. Geophys. Res., 97 (D14), p. 15918; Thibert, E., Dominé, F., (1997) J. Phys. Chem., 101, p. 3554; Livingston, F.E., George, S.E., (2001) J. Phys. Chem., 105 (21), p. 5155; Huthwelker, T., (1999) Experimente und Modellierung der Spurengasaufnahme in Eis, , Dissertation Universität Bonn, Cuviellier Verlag, Göttingen; Carslaw, K.C., Clegg, S.L., Brimblecombe, P., (1995) J. Phys. Chem., 99, p. 11557; Daniel, Ch., (1998) H+ and He+ backscattering from ice, , Master Thesis in Physics, University at Albany; McDonald, J.E., (1965) J. Geophys. Res., 70 (6), p. 1553; Gross, G.J., (1995) J. Colloid Interface Sci., 25, p. 270; Nye, J.F., (1991) J. Cryst. Growth, 113, p. 465; Brown, W.L., Augustyniak, W.M., Lanzerotti, L.J., Johnson, R.D., Evat, R., (1980) Phys. Rev. Lett., 45 (20), p. 1332","Huthwelker, T.; Physics Department, University at Albany, State University of New York, 1400 Washington Avenue, Albany, NY 12222, United States; email: huthw@atmos.umnw.ethz.ch",,,,,,,,0168583X,,NIMBE,,"English","Nucl Instrum Methods Phys Res Sect B",Conference Paper,Scopus,2-s2.0-0036568977
